Description: CVE-2026-4873 - Do not reuse a non-TLS STARTTLS connection if new requires TLS
 A flaw in curl allows connections requiring TLS to incorrectly reuse
 unencrypted connections from the same connection pool. When initial
 transfers use IMAP, SMTP, or POP3 protocols, a subsequent request to
 the same host may bypass the TLS requirement and transmit data
 unencrypted. This patch adds a req_tls flag to the connection matching
 logic to prevent reusing non-TLS STARTTLS connections when TLS is
 required.
 .
