Description: CVE-2026-5545 - Fix connection reuse on negotiate
 A logical error in libcurl's connection pooling mechanism allows improper
 reuse of HTTP Negotiate (SPNEGO) authenticated connections. When an
 application performs Negotiate authentication to a server and then makes
 another request to the same host with different credentials, libcurl may
 wrongfully reuse the previous connection. This patch adds negotiate state
 validation to the url_match_auth_ntlm() function alongside the existing
 NTLM state check.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/33e43985b8f3b9e66691d06e70be0395849856cd
Author: Stefan Eissing <stefan@eissing.org>
Last-Update: 2026-05-01

